00:00.000 --> 00:07.840
Here's how to update drivers on your PowerEdge 
server using a Dell Update Package, or DUP.

00:07.840 --> 00:12.880
Go to dell.com/support and enter your 
systems service tag, or click 'Browse

00:12.880 --> 00:22.480
all Products' to select it manually.
Select 'Drivers and Downloads',

00:22.480 --> 00:30.880
and choose the OS you have installed.
Under 'Download Type' select 'Driver', then under

00:30.880 --> 00:40.160
'Category' select the type of driver you need.
Expand the listed drivers for more details,

00:40.160 --> 00:45.360
and optionally click the 'View 
full driver details' link.

00:45.360 --> 00:53.600
Click 'Download' to save the DUP.
For Windows, right click the DUP

00:53.600 --> 00:59.280
and select 'Run as Administrator'.
Review the release notes, then click

00:59.280 --> 01:18.480
'Install' to start the update.
Thanks for watching

